    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - MAINTENANCE - Bleeding the Fuel System</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Bleeding the Fuel System</title>
        <figure id="f1603723" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/g1603723.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 23. Bleeding the Fuel System</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>To bleed the fuel system, proceed as follows:</para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Loosen injection line nuts (using 17mm wrench).</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Attempt to start the unit. Once fuel is observed, tighten both injector line nuts one at a time.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The system will automatically attempt 3 start cycles. If it fails to start after 3 cycles, it will
                    stop and display an "Over crank" message on the control panel display. Simply reset the system by
                    pressing the START/STOP button. Press the START/STOP button again to re-initiate the start cycle.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
